NAME - ::<namespace>:: emulation_pbb_trunk_config

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

This procedure configures Trunk properties.

List arguments in the alphabetical order or in the reverse alphabetical order.

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-bridge_handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

The value of the -bridge_handle parameter must be a bridge handle returned by ::::emulation_pbb_config procedure. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxN.

DEFAULT

 None

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M]

DESCRIPTION

Action to perform. This parameter is supported using the following create - Create new Trunk on -port_handle.modify - Modify Trunk specified with -handle parameter.enable - Enable Trunk specified with -handle parameter.disable - Disable Trunk specified with -handle parameter.remove - Remove Trunk specified with -handle parameter.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork

Sets the MD Name format for the trunk. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxN. none - string - Parameter -name is used to configure the MD Name. Use '?' to configure wildcard.mac_plus_2_octets - Parameter -name is used to configure MD Name (MAC Address format plus two octets, e.g. 00:11:22:33:44:55:66:77) .

DEFAULT
